Definition: shockingly brutal or cruel
Example: murder is an atrocious crime; a grievous offense against morality; a grievous crime; no excess was too monstrous for them to commit
Synonyms: noun, attribute, atrocity, act, atrociousness, flagitious, grievous, monstrous, person, monster, event, monstrosity, shockingly, brutal, or, cruel, murder, is, an, crime, a, offense, against, morality, no, excess, was, too, for, them, to, commit
Category: adj.all
